President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring September 2012 as National Alcohol and Drug Addiction Recovery Month. The proclamation acknowledges the millions of Americans who are in recovery from substance use disorders and emphasizes the importance of supporting their journey. The administration is committed to advancing evidence-based recovery solutions and has worked to strengthen substance abuse prevention and treatment programs. The proclamation also calls for the removal of barriers to recovery and the promotion of early intervention to break the cycle of drug abuse and incarceration. The president encourages the American people to observe the month with appropriate programs, ceremonies, and activities.